snippet: The police said that 47 police officers were injured Sunday when Protestant protesters angered by a Catholic parade in northern Belfast threw homemade bombs, bricks and fireworks.
abstract: Forty-seven police officers are injured when Protestant protesters angered by a Catholic parade in Belfast, Northern Ireland, throw homemade bombs, bricks and fireworks.
lead_paragraph: The police said that 47 police officers were injured Sunday when Protestant protesters angered by a Catholic parade in northern Belfast threw homemade bombs, bricks and fireworks.

headline.seo: Clash Injures 47 Police Officers in Belfast
headline.main: Northern Ireland: Protesters Injure Police Officers in Belfast
headline.print_headline: Northern Ireland: Protesters Injure Police Officers in Belfast
